jnxJsAuthMIB.name: jnxJsAuthMIB
jnxJsAuthMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net HTTP://www.juniper.net
jnxJsAuthMIB.description: Firewall and security features restrict the accessing of protected resources (ideally on different zones) behind a firewall based on their source ip and other credentials. This module defines the objects pertain to access authentication.

jnxJsFwAuthNumPendingUsers.name: jnxJsFwAuthNumPendingUsers
jnxJsFwAuthNumPendingUsers.description: Number of users currently waiting to be authenticated by the firewall user authentication mechanism.

jnxJsFwAuthNumSuccUsers.name: jnxJsFwAuthNumSuccUsers
jnxJsFwAuthNumSuccUsers.description: Number of users currently allowed access by the firewall user authentication mechanism.

jnxJsFwAuthNumFailedUsers.name: jnxJsFwAuthNumFailedUsers
jnxJsFwAuthNumFailedUsers.description: Number of users currently failed to be authenticated by the firewall user authentication mechanism.

jnxJsFwAuthTotalUsers.name: jnxJsFwAuthTotalUsers
jnxJsFwAuthTotalUsers.description: Total number of users that are accessing or attempting to access resources managed by the firewall user authentication mechanism.

jnxJsFwAuthUserName.name: jnxJsFwAuthUserName
jnxJsFwAuthUserName.description: The name of the user who is attempting or has been authenticated.

jnxJsFwAuthServiceDesc.name: jnxJsFwAuthServiceDesc
jnxJsFwAuthServiceDesc.description: The service or application name that the enthentication is performed for: telnet, ftp, http.

jnxJsFwAuthReason.name: jnxJsFwAuthReason
jnxJsFwAuthReason.description: The reason for the trap being generated: authentication failure due to: timeout, invalid password, invalid username, etc.

jnxJsFwAuthFailure.name: jnxJsFwAuthFailure
jnxJsFwAuthFailure.description: A firewall user authentication status trap signifies whether a user using the pass-through firewall authentication mechanism has been rejected due to reason specified in the trap. jnxJsFwAuthUserName is the user. jnxClientIPAddress is the ip address the user came from. jnxJsFwAuthServiceDesc specifies the application by which the authentication was performed. jnxJsFwAuthReason indicates the reason for failure.

jnxJsFwAuthServiceUp.name: jnxJsFwAuthServiceUp
jnxJsFwAuthServiceUp.description: Firewall user authentication service has started.

jnxJsFwAuthServiceDown.name: jnxJsFwAuthServiceDown
jnxJsFwAuthServiceDown.description: Firewall user authentication service has stopped.

jnxJsFwAuthCapacityExceeded.name: jnxJsFwAuthCapacityExceeded
jnxJsFwAuthCapacityExceeded.description: Firewall user authentication maximum capacity has been exceeded. jnxJsFwAuthTotalUsers indicates the total number of users being authenticated. And it has exceeds the maximum allowable users.
